GISP2 Meltwater Laser-Light Scattering Dust Concentration Profile Data


Laser Light Scattering (LLS) from meltwater was used to
obtain dust concentrations along the top 120 m of the
GISP2 B core. In this technique, the intensity of light
scattered at 90 degrees from the meltwater sample is
proportional to the amount of dust suspended in the
meltwater. The resulting dust profile was then
converted from depth to age using the GISP2 depth-age
scale (Meese et al., 1997, The Greenland Ice Sheet
Project 2 depth-age scale: Methods and results,
Journal of Geophysical Research 102:26411-26423).
Details of the LLS from Meltwater technique are given
in Ram et al., 1994.
